|> 
|> Personally, I think this is completely stupid.  In my day, a major
|> version number change on the outside of the box meant there was a major
|> technological change inside the box, like a complete rewrite.  These
|> kids today think that every release has to be a major version number
|> change, and that the only numbers that can follow the decial point are 0
|> and 1 (like 2.0, 2.1, 2.11).  Now OS/2 1.3 to OS/2 2.0, there was a
