|> --> Kent Lundberg, Grumpy Old Man.

What is important is marketing hype, not how new the source code is.
Remember NT 3.1?  I bet the 3.1 version number sold more copies than
the letters NT.  I NEVER buy version 1.0 of anything.  If a person didn't
know that NT was new, it would look like a stable product.

OS/2 is competing with Windows 3.1 and 4.0.  OS/2 has been a superior 
product for years, but hasn't become the market leader.  Why?  Marketing.

I hope IBM continues to agressively market OS/2.  And that means keeping
up with the version number hype.  PLEASE, make it version 3.0.

Alan Scott

